Step 1: Install Apache Tomcat
Step 2: Download tomcat packages from https://tomcat.apache.org/download-80.cgi onto /opt on EC2 instance
wget (tomcat URL)
Step 3: Unzip downloaded tomcat tar
tar -xzvf (tar file)
Step 4: After tomcat unzipped, you can check all tomcat binary files bin folder
Step 5: Check startup.sh / shutdown.sh to start and stop tomcat server.
Java must be installed before starting tomcat server
./startup.sh---It will start your tomcat server
Check tomcate URL using IP Address with tomcat port :8080
$(dirname $(readlink -f $(which javac))-To check Java JDK path
Step 6: If we want we can add Java path in below linux default file i.e  .bash_profile 
To Set Path in Linux: .bash_profile
